error: internal compiler error: unexpected panic

note: the compiler unexpectedly panicked. this is a bug.

note: we would appreciate a bug report: https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/new?labels=C-bug%2C+I-ICE%2C+T-compiler&template=ice.md

note: rustc 1.51.0 (2fd73fabe 2021-03-23) running on x86_64-apple-darwin

query stack during panic:
#0 [mir_borrowck] borrow-checking `main`
#1 [analysis] running analysis passes on this crate
end of query stack
```

Here the program that I tried to compile:

```
use std::env;


fn hash_files(file_names: &Vec<String>, line_formatter: &mut dyn FnMut(&String, &String) -> String) {
    for i in file_names {
        let hash = "abcdef".to_string();
        let line_out = line_formatter(i, &hash);

        println!("{}", line_out);
    }
}

fn main() {
    let args: Vec<String> = env::args().skip(1).collect();
    
    if args.len() == 0 {
        println!("usage: rs256shum <file_name> [<file_name> ...]");
    }

    let simple_format = |f_name: &String, hash_val: &String| -> String {
        return format!("{}  {}", f_name, hash_val);
    };

    hash_files(&args, &mut simple_format);
}
```
As far as I can tell the program is in fact invalid as the variable `simple_format` should be mutable as it is borrowed as mutable in the function call following its definition. If this definition is replaced by 

```
    let mut simple_format = |f_name: &String, hash_val: &String| -> String {
        return format!("{}  {}", f_name, hash_val);
    };
```

the program compiles.
